-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

---:[ Requires

- Perl
- Net::RawIP Module [ http://www.cpan.org ]
- TK module [ http://www.cpan.org ]
- libpcap [ http://www.tcpdump.org ]


---:[ Disclaimer

THIS PROJECT WAS DEVELOPED FOR TESTING AND DEMONSTRATION PURPOSE ONLY! 
THE AUTHORS DONT FEEL RESPONSIBLE FOR ILLEGAL ABUSE OF THIS PIECE OF 
SOFTWARE AND WE ADVICE YOU TO USE IT LEGALLY AND DO NOT BREAK THE LAW!


---:[ Description

ip-packet is a TCP / UDP / ICMP / ARP Packetgenerator written in Perl. 
It contains a GUI frontend, an interactive and a parameter driven shell 
interface.
You can create packets using (nearly) all available header options of the
chosen protocol.
Additionally you can bruteforce some header options like source and destination
ports and icmp code and type and use a config file to configure your packet. 


---:[ Installation

If your system supports Perl just install the required modules and run
./ip-packet.pl --help for help.


---:[ Usage

To use the GUI version run ip-packet.pl --gui
To use the interactive shell interface run ip-packtet.pl --interactive
You can speicfy a config file using --conf
Execute ip-packet.pl --params to get a list of all params, --help will
provider you with some help.


---:[ The documentation

The RFCs of the protocols can be found in the doc directory.
Additionally there is a short text about the TCP flags and ICMP types.
Or read the hijackerguide by Stefan Krecher.

